<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Bootstrap 4 Scrollspy Task</title>
    
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@4.6.2/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css">
    
    <style>
        body { position: relative; } /* Required for Scrollspy */
        section { height: 80vh; padding: 100px 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; }
        .navbar { position: sticky; top: 0; z-index: 1000; }
        #home { background-color: #e9ecef; }
        #about { background-color: #dee2e6; }
        #contact { background-color: #ced4da; }
    </style>
</head>

<body data-spy="scroll" data-target="#mainNav" data-offset="70">

    <nav id="mainNav" class="navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-dark bg-dark">
        <a class="navbar-brand" href="#">ScrollSpy Demo</a>
        <div class="collapse navbar-collapse" id="navbarNav">
            <ul class="nav nav-pills">
                <li class="nav-item"><a class="nav-link active" href="#home">Home</a></li>
                <li class="nav-item"><a class="nav-link" href="#about">About</a></li>
                <li class="nav-item"><a class="nav-link" href="#contact">Contact</a></li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </nav>

    <section id="home">
        <h1>Home Section</h1>
        <p>Scroll down to see the navigation menu automatically highlight the active section.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="about">
        <h1>About Section</h1>
        <p>Bootstrap 4 monitors the scroll position and updates the 'active' class on nav links.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="contact">
        <h1>Contact Section</h1>
        <p>This provides a smooth, modern user experience for single-page applications.</p>
    </section>

    <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.5.1.slim.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@4.6.2/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>

</body>
</html>
